@node "INTRO" "Introduccion a newNET"
@next "REQUI"
@prev "Main"

                           INTRODUCTION

     If you use YamNet, @{b}newNET@{ub} is programed to replace it.

      "newNET"  is  other program to avoid expensive direct phone
     callings  between  points  and BBS of fidonet-like networks.
     Saving  in long-distant calls and using the way more used of
     the moment:  Internet.

      "newNET" allows to phone automaticly to Internet, send FIDO
     "mail"  files in e-mails using SMTP and to get choosing only
     the  files  generated  by  the  program,  via POP3 (E-Mail),
     without the need of use any concrete E-Mail program; decodes
     files and imports it using the user selected "Fido-Mailer".

      "newNET"  can be used by any  user without the need of that
     the  receiver have newNET installed in the system; Receivers
     can  use  any  standard  MIME E-Mail program to deattach the
     mail files to the INBOUND directory of their system.

      "newNET"  converts  configuration  file  of its predecesor,
     YamNet  to  the  most  modern  newNET @{"configuration" link "CONFIG" 0}.

      "newNET"  deletes  old files that are already sent when has
     passed  a  determinated  number  of  days.  Re-send archived
     files if their are requested in the case of decoding error.

    ------------------------------------------------------------
             newNET is @{b}*Freeware*@{ub} © Alfredo Soro, 1997
       The author is not liable about any damage that could be
     done by this software. newNET is NOT tested on animals. :-)
@endnode

